    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7<strong> </strong>and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tortiglioni for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite then drain</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will go in the oven later!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop <strong>half </strong>your <strong>prosciutto </strong>finely (you'll use the rest later!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated cheese</strong> with your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a pot and mix until fully combined</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> </strong>250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to the pot and stir it all together</p><p>Cook over a medium heat for 4-6 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and the sauce has thickened slightly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, remove from the heat</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> to the sauce with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and the <strong>chopped prosciutto</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>croque monsieur sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained tortiglioni</strong> to the sauce</p><p>Stir it all together and add to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top with the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>reserved prosciutto slices</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 10-12 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>croque monsieur pasta bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your<strong> cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining Dijon mustard</strong> with your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>in a large bowl \u2013 this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> salad </strong>and<strong> sliced cucumber </strong>to the dressing and toss \u2013 this is your <strong>bistro salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/croque-monsieur-pasta-bake-with-bistro-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> croque monsieur pasta bake</strong> with the <strong>bistro salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
